Russia’s Spring Grain Sowing Grew 8.6%, Rosstat Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-06-17T08:02:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/russia-s-spring-grain-sowing-grew-8-6-rosstat-says-table-.html
Russia’s spring grain sowing was 8.6
percent higher at 27.6 million hectares (68.2 million acres) as
of June 1 compared with a year earlier, Russia’s State
Statistical Service said in an e-mail today.  The following table gives sowing areas and winter crops
losses in thousands of hectares as of June 1 compared with the
same date last year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
